If I Were Creating the First Prototype
I would build only these 5 components:
Mock Alert Generator
Alert Queue Screen
AI Classification Engine (rule-based initially)
Action Engine (Close / Watch / Assign)
Dashboard
Skip for now:
Salesforce integration
Real SSH access
Real log retrieval
Gemma/Ollama
Approval workflow
RAG ingestion
Audit database
These can be simulated with sample data.
The goal of the first demo is not to prove the technology.
The goal is to make leadership see:
"An alert comes in, AI analyses it, decides what to do, takes action, and shows the result on a dashboard."
